N:agent-principles
D:Use this skill when a user needs the baseline habits for working well with AI coding agents: break work down, keep context clean, choose plan versus execute depth, automate repeated work, and verify outputs. Triggers on: agent principles, AI collaboration principles, context management, divide and conquer, plan vs execute, verify AI output.
G:agentic-development principles context-management automation multi-agent
U[6]:
  Confirm baseline collaboration principles for AI-agent work
  Break broad requests into smaller verified steps
  Keep context fresh with session hygiene and handoff notes
  Choose the right plan-versus-execute depth
  Spot repetition that should become automation
  Verify outputs before trusting them
R[4]:
  Route daily workflow mechanics to agent-workflow
  Route configuration and permissions setup to agent-configuration
  Keep the entrypoint focused on principles, not platform trivia
  Use references for deep examples instead of bloating the main file
S[4]{n,action}:
  1,Confirm the request belongs to the principles surface
  2,Apply the six-principle checklist
  3,Recommend the smallest useful correction
  4,Route adjacent jobs to the narrower sibling skill
